==English==

==Etymology==
"p.o." (initials for "[[piss off]]", make someone annoyed, exasperated or angry) + 'ed

===Adjective===
# (''slang'') [[pissed off|Pissed off]].
#* ''Wow. No reason to get so '''p.o.'ed''' at me. All I'm doing is trying to help you.''

===Verb===
# (''slang'') [[pissed off|Pissed off]].
#* ''All the noise in the classroom really '''p.o.'ed''' me; I couldn't hear the teacher give out the  problem.''